title: Tomi Lahren Smacks Down Maher Guest Who Tries to Call Her Out on Benghazi
text:
Tomi Lahren Smacks Down Maher Guest Who Tries to Call Her Out on Benghazi by Josh Feldman | 1:21 pm, February 4th, 2017 video 
During last night’s Real Time , a Democratic guest on Bill Maher ‘s panel challenged Tomi Lahren on Benghazi and she quickly fired back. 
As Maher brought up the Yemen raid, he observed that had it turned out exactly the same––with civilians and a Navy SEAL dying in the raid––and Hillary Clinton was the president instead, “this would be the new Benghazi.” 
Lahren agreed, but then they ended up getting into a back-and-forth over whether Benghazi was “bullshit,” as Maher put it. 
Jason Kander , an Army veteran and former Missouri Secretary of State, told Lahren that a lot of people “used the people who died as political chess pieces” and she challenged her to name all four of the men who died in Benghazi, telling her, “You don’t know.” 
Well, as it happens, Lahren did know, and she listed off the names of all four Benghazi victims for him. 
Watch above, via HBO.
